<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="312" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,476,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[614,662,477,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">type</typeStatus>
locality, Serra da 
<taxonomicName box="[870,988,476,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Apopyllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gandarela">Gandarela</taxonomicName>
, Rio Acima, 
<collectingRegion box="[1139,1293,476,501]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1306,1374,476,501]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1960,1982]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,409,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,409,1939]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 14. Geographic distribution records of Apopyllus species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261087/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
D). The 
<typeStatus box="[277,325,512,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">type</typeStatus>
locality is an area of Canga, a mountain field vegetation typical of iron-ore plateaus (
<bibRefCitation author="Salgado" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" refString="Salgado, A. A. R. &amp; do Carmo, F. F. (2015) ' Quadrilatero Ferrifero': A Beautiful and Neglected Landscape Between the Gold and Iron Ore Reservoirs. In: Landscapes and Landforms of Brazil. Springer, Dordrecht, pp. 319 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 94 - 017 - 8023 - 0 _ 29" type="book chapter" year="2015">Salgado &amp; Carmo 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
